76
00:06:13,980 --> 00:06:15,501
You had divorced once.

77
00:06:15,581 --> 00:06:17,304
What now?
You decide never to marry again?

78
00:06:18,221 --> 00:06:18,901
Oh my.

79
00:06:18,981 --> 00:06:20,420
A contract?

80
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:21,741
You're really ridiculous.

81
00:06:21,821 --> 00:06:23,141
Just go ahead.

82
00:06:23,781 --> 00:06:25,540
It's not like I've never been married.

83
00:06:25,620 --> 00:06:26,821
I've been through it.

84
00:06:28,261 --> 00:06:29,180
The marriage

85
00:06:29,261 --> 00:06:31,021
is a security for women.

86
00:06:32,740 --> 00:06:33,340
In my opinion,

87
00:06:33,420 --> 00:06:34,182
our own brains

88
00:06:34,262 --> 00:06:35,620
is a security for women.

89
00:06:36,021 --> 00:06:37,300
Even marriage laws

90
00:06:37,380 --> 00:06:39,420
couldn't protect me
if I'm being foolish.

91
00:06:41,581 --> 00:06:42,581
How about this?

92
00:06:42,781 --> 00:06:43,701
I'll go to Li Xiaoxiao

93
00:06:43,781 --> 00:06:44,781
and register for you.

94
00:06:44,980 --> 00:06:46,340
You find a reliable old man

95
00:06:46,420 --> 00:06:47,660
and get a security.

96
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:48,941
You girl!

97
00:06:49,021 --> 00:06:50,061
At my age,

98
00:06:50,141 --> 00:06:51,380
I don't need a man anymore.

99
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:52,341
With my pension,

100
00:06:52,421 --> 00:06:53,420
I'll act as his nanny?

101
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:54,980
You!

102
00:06:55,180 --> 00:06:55,861
See?

103
00:06:55,941 --> 00:06:57,180
I'm following suit.

104
00:06:57,461 --> 00:06:58,141
You don't

105
00:06:58,221 --> 00:06:58,702
get married.

106
00:06:58,782 --> 00:07:00,261
Why force me to?

107
00:07:01,101 --> 00:07:03,581
Mei Chengyi is really

108
00:07:03,781 --> 00:07:05,420
a nice guy.

109
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:08,100
We just talked about
finding an apartment,

110
00:07:08,180 --> 00:07:09,180
and now,

111
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:11,180
he's cleaned up the house.

112
00:07:12,221 --> 00:07:13,461
But our lease agreement

113
00:07:14,021 --> 00:07:15,540
still has half a month left.

114
00:07:15,901 --> 00:07:17,180
It'd be a loss of money.

115
00:07:17,781 --> 00:07:18,860
The school of Dami

116
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:20,461
is not far from here.

117
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:22,940
But Xiaomi's kindergarten

118
00:07:23,141 --> 00:07:24,341
is not nearby.

119
00:07:25,461 --> 00:07:27,180
Change Xiaomi's kindergarten.

120
00:07:28,141 --> 00:07:30,060
Perfect, we can keep Qian Hao away.

121
00:08:08,701 --> 00:08:10,701
This is the cemetery
that You Xin is buried.

122
00:08:11,221 --> 00:08:12,781
Why is Youyou here?

123
00:08:13,461 --> 00:08:14,461
She doesn't go to work,

124
00:08:14,661 --> 00:08:15,701
but to see her sister?

125
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:17,182
She doesn't know

126
00:08:17,262 --> 00:08:18,740
her sister's cemetery is here.

127
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:20,221
She has never been here.

128
00:08:20,540 --> 00:08:22,261
Maybe Chengyi told her.

129
00:08:23,740 --> 00:08:24,821
Stop guessing.

130
00:08:25,021 --> 00:08:26,620
We'll know then.

131
00:08:35,352 --> 00:08:39,640
(Yongshou Cemetery)

132
00:08:40,660 --> 00:08:41,941
Why are you here?

133
00:08:49,341 --> 00:08:51,221
Complaining to me won't help.

134
00:08:56,620 --> 00:08:57,620
Hurry up.

135
00:09:01,020 --> 00:09:02,260
Here she is.

136
00:09:02,660 --> 00:09:04,501
Complaining to me won't help.

137
00:09:04,581 --> 00:09:05,741
Master always gives customers

138
00:09:05,821 --> 00:09:06,780
a personal concert

139
00:09:06,860 --> 00:09:08,740
with just one song.

140
00:09:09,701 --> 00:09:11,381
Perhaps one day,
someone with a bad temper

141
00:09:11,461 --> 00:09:13,260
might come up from the grave to hit him.

142
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:17,500
Let's go.

143
00:09:21,341 --> 00:09:22,341
Let's go.

144
00:09:48,860 --> 00:09:49,860
Xin,

145
00:09:51,061 --> 00:09:52,461
be happy today.

146
00:09:53,221 --> 00:09:54,541
Chengyi criticized me.

147
00:09:55,140 --> 00:09:55,781
Later,

148
00:09:55,861 --> 00:09:56,820
I'll have someone

149
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:57,861
to repaint the words

150
00:09:57,941 --> 00:09:59,341
on your tombstone.

151
00:10:00,221 --> 00:10:01,541
Now, I

152
00:10:02,660 --> 00:10:04,260
(You Xin)
am a manager now.

153
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:26,500
She doesn't go to work,

154
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:29,020
but comes to visit her sister's grave.

155
00:10:29,980 --> 00:10:31,421
She still hasn't let go.

156
00:10:33,821 --> 00:10:34,860
Who can let go?

157
00:10:35,581 --> 00:10:37,020
Can we?

158
00:10:39,701 --> 00:10:41,060
We are not short of money,

159
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:43,020
not to mention her salary.

160
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:45,421
She can take a leave.

161
00:10:45,660 --> 00:10:47,620
Just let the company dock her pay.

162
00:10:49,380 --> 00:10:50,660
Let's go back.

163
00:10:51,301 --> 00:10:52,301
For what?

164
00:10:53,660 --> 00:10:55,660
We have to wait here.

165
00:10:55,860 --> 00:10:57,501
She might go to work

166
00:10:57,581 --> 00:10:59,061
after this.

167
00:11:00,260 --> 00:11:01,461
Don't let her notice us.

168
00:11:16,181 --> 00:11:17,421
I'm going to work.

169
00:11:17,581 --> 00:11:18,701
I'll come see you tomorrow.

170
00:11:22,301 --> 00:11:23,421
She's leaving.

171
00:11:42,860 --> 00:11:43,860
Come on.

172
00:11:55,461 --> 00:11:56,461
Dad.

173
00:12:00,541 --> 00:12:01,860
(Ten teaching characteristics)
Is Grandma okay?

174
00:12:02,421 --> 00:12:03,221
Hello.

175
00:12:03,341 --> 00:12:04,341
Hello.

176
00:12:04,541 --> 00:12:05,660
I am his dad.

177
00:12:06,181 --> 00:12:07,221
His grandma is sick,

178
00:12:07,301 --> 00:12:08,501
so I have to take him back.

179
00:12:08,581 --> 00:12:09,421
Please wait a moment.

180
00:12:09,501 --> 00:12:11,021
I'll contact Xiaomi's mom.

181
00:12:11,101 --> 00:12:11,581
No need.

182
00:12:11,661 --> 00:12:12,700
I am his dad.

183
00:12:12,780 --> 00:12:14,021
I have the right to take him.

184
00:12:14,101 --> 00:12:14,700
Wait.

185
00:12:14,780 --> 00:12:15,222
His mom

186
00:12:15,302 --> 00:12:16,420
has informed us.

187
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:18,140
She's the only one to pick up the child.

188
00:12:18,140 --> 00:12:18,660
I must

189
00:12:18,740 --> 00:12:19,540
tell her everything.

190
00:12:19,620 --> 00:12:20,540
No need.

191
00:12:20,620 --> 00:12:21,022
Sir,

192
00:12:21,102 --> 00:12:22,500
you can't just take him away.

193
00:12:22,740 --> 00:12:23,301
Sir,

194
00:12:23,381 --> 00:12:24,341
please put him down.

195
00:12:24,421 --> 00:12:25,539
I need to call her.

196
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:25,861
Okay?

197
00:12:25,941 --> 00:12:26,941
Sir.

198
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:29,500
Security!

199
00:12:30,341 --> 00:12:31,341
Security!

200
00:12:33,581 --> 00:12:34,581
Security!

201
00:12:35,061 --> 00:12:36,061
Security!

202
00:12:41,140 --> 00:12:42,660
Stop the car.

203
00:12:45,421 --> 00:12:46,621
Open it.

204
00:12:46,701 --> 00:12:47,860
Child.

205
00:12:48,980 --> 00:12:49,980
Sir.

206
00:12:53,860 --> 00:12:54,421
Now,

207
00:12:54,501 --> 00:12:55,900
why don't you pick up the call?

208
00:13:27,020 --> 00:13:28,020
Master.

209
00:13:28,860 --> 00:13:29,740
I'm back.

210
00:13:29,860 --> 00:13:30,860
Welcome back.

211
00:13:31,541 --> 00:13:32,541
Let's go?

212
00:13:32,780 --> 00:13:33,540
Let's go.

213
00:13:33,620 --> 00:13:34,620
Let's go.

214
00:13:41,941 --> 00:13:42,941
Grandpa.

215
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:44,860
Xiaomi.

216
00:13:46,701 --> 00:13:48,140
Didn't he go to kindergarten?

217
00:13:49,421 --> 00:13:50,701
My mom is like this.

218
00:13:50,941 --> 00:13:52,021
He is my son,

219
00:13:52,101 --> 00:13:53,421
so he must stay here.

220
00:13:54,221 --> 00:13:55,580
Does Xu Kaixin agree on it?

221
00:13:55,660 --> 00:13:56,701
I don't care that much.

222
00:13:57,900 --> 00:13:59,421
You are hiding it from her?

223
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:03,941
You're really looking for trouble.

224
00:14:04,101 --> 00:14:04,781
He's a child.

225
00:14:04,861 --> 00:14:06,101
What's the point?

226
00:14:06,181 --> 00:14:07,660
You hide it

227
00:14:07,740 --> 00:14:08,541
from her.

228
00:14:08,621 --> 00:14:10,141
Aren't you intensifying the conflict?

229
00:14:10,221 --> 00:14:11,221
So what?

230
00:14:11,301 --> 00:14:13,061
She had been my wife for a few years.

231
00:14:13,380 --> 00:14:15,101
My mom was her mother-in-law, right?

232
00:14:15,181 --> 00:14:16,420
I didn't ask her

233
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:17,500
to stay here.

234
00:14:19,780 --> 00:14:21,061
My mom loves Xiaomi.

235
00:14:21,421 --> 00:14:22,421
If he's staying here,

236
00:14:22,701 --> 00:14:24,101
maybe my mom can wake up earlier.

237
00:14:25,821 --> 00:14:28,101
Dad, I'm hungry.
I want to eat something.

238
00:14:30,020 --> 00:14:31,660
Dad, give him some bread.

239
00:14:31,740 --> 00:14:32,740
Yes.

240
00:14:34,660 --> 00:14:35,381
Eat some bread.

241
00:14:35,461 --> 00:14:36,461
No.

242
00:14:36,660 --> 00:14:37,860
I want to eat noodles.

243
00:14:38,860 --> 00:14:40,140
I'll buy you some later, okay?

244
00:14:40,980 --> 00:14:42,541
But I want to eat now.

245
00:14:42,740 --> 00:14:43,981
Eat bread now.

246
00:14:44,061 --> 00:14:45,221
No way.

247
00:14:45,581 --> 00:14:46,621
I need to go back.

248
00:14:46,701 --> 00:14:48,900
I want to find Miss. Find my mom.

249
00:14:49,061 --> 00:14:49,660
You!

250
00:14:49,740 --> 00:14:50,461
What's wrong?

251
00:14:50,541 --> 00:14:51,420
Where are you going?

252
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:53,060
No. I don't want to be here.

253
00:14:53,140 --> 00:14:53,621
Come on.

254
00:14:53,701 --> 00:14:54,421
Why hit him?

255
00:14:54,501 --> 00:14:55,501
Why?

256
00:14:55,581 --> 00:14:56,621
Alright, don't cry.

257
00:14:56,701 --> 00:14:58,061
He knows nothing.

258
00:14:58,301 --> 00:14:59,660
I hate Dad.

259
00:14:59,821 --> 00:15:00,660
Alright.

260
00:15:00,740 --> 00:15:01,821
I'll go buy it.

261
00:15:02,140 --> 00:15:03,900
I told you.

262
00:15:03,980 --> 00:15:04,622
You insist

263
00:15:04,702 --> 00:15:06,101
on taking him from his mom.

264
00:15:06,341 --> 00:15:07,421
You can't take care of him.

265
00:15:07,421 --> 00:15:09,021
Why vent your anger at him?

266
00:15:09,101 --> 00:15:10,060
Oh, my!

267
00:15:10,140 --> 00:15:11,541
Okay, I will buy it for you.

268
00:15:13,020 --> 00:15:14,221
Oh, my!

269
00:15:14,341 --> 00:15:15,740
Come on, don't cry.

270
00:15:19,860 --> 00:15:20,860
Come back soon!

271
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:28,222
I think...

272
00:15:28,302 --> 00:15:29,381
Stop it. Do your work.

273
00:15:29,461 --> 00:15:31,101
We should stock up

274
00:15:31,341 --> 00:15:31,982
more

275
00:15:32,062 --> 00:15:34,101
small ceramic figurines
of boys and girls,

276
00:15:34,260 --> 00:15:35,500
small wreaths,

277
00:15:35,620 --> 00:15:36,580
and gold ingots.

278
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:37,142
Right.

279
00:15:37,222 --> 00:15:38,420
And small incense burners.

280
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:39,500
Those sell the best.

281
00:15:40,260 --> 00:15:41,341
I am so worried.

282
00:15:41,421 --> 00:15:42,342
When

283
00:15:42,422 --> 00:15:43,420
those festivals coming,

284
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:44,981
my rhinitis flare up.

285
00:15:45,061 --> 00:15:45,781
Yiersan

286
00:15:45,861 --> 00:15:47,660
even gets gastroenteritis.

287
00:15:48,980 --> 00:15:50,101
Civilized rituals.

288
00:15:50,541 --> 00:15:52,061
I think we need to offer some flowers.

289
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:54,500
Like those small flowers
you gave your sister.

290
00:15:54,581 --> 00:15:55,941
I think they are quite good.

291
00:15:56,660 --> 00:15:58,021
If it were me,

292
00:15:58,101 --> 00:16:00,221
I would place the Calabash Brothers.

293
00:16:00,461 --> 00:16:02,021
It's lively and festive.

